The paper discusses the measurement of scholarly impact and visibility on the Web, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL), social networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), social computing (cs.SOC), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The focus on social Web impact and the use of Mendeley as a reference manager suggest a stronger connection to cs.DL and cs.SI, but the broader discussion of scholarly communication and online presence could also fit into the other categories.
